The paper deals with algorithms for computing Abelian periods of words, which is a problem in string algorithms. The paper discusses time and space complexity of the algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of a select function, which is a common tool in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical performance of the algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
